	<Language_en_US>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_EXOTIC_UNIT_THALAI_THIRVAI">
			<Text>[ICON_IDEOLOGY_AUTOCRACY] Thalai Thirvai</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_EXOTIC_UNIT_THALAI_THIRVAI_HELP">
			<Text>Fast Medieval Mercenary ranged naval unit. Price shown is how much it costs to hire this unit for 20 turns.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_EXOTIC_UNIT_THALAI_THIRVAI_STRATEGY">
			<Text>
				Use the Thalai Thirvai to lead your ships against your enemies on the high seas. It receives the Great Admiral, Logistics, and Supply promotions when hired. This means it provides +15% Combat bonus to all Ships within 2 tiles, 1 additional attack per turn, and allows the unit to heal 15 HP damage per turn even when outside of Friendly Territory.		
			</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_EXOTIC_UNIT_THALAI_THIRVAI_PEDIA">
			<Text>
				The Thalai Thirvai is a Medieval era Mercenary ranged naval unit, available upon the discovery of Astronomy. The Harbor is required for this unit to be built. The Thalai Thirvai becomes obsolete upon the discovery of Steam Power.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]
				Admirals of the Chola Navy held many ranks within its highly organized administration. One of the most important offices was the Thalai, or head, and Thirvai, or duty, the overseer of the customs department which was mainly responsible for trade and tariffs. This unit of Chola bureaucracy employed only the best merchants and professional economists of the empire, tasked with calculating duties and other financial obligations of trade partners. They also assessed the prices of commodities, depending on seasons and trade route length. Other arms of Chola customs force included intelligence corps, armed naval vessels tasked with police duties, a coast guard and even privateer squads.
			</Text>
		</Row>
	</Language_en_US>	
  
